Review of Rebuild, Renew: Chapter 1

The concept is nice, giving me Last of Us/Kaiserreich vibes wth the whole second US civil war and collapse.

What I feel really holding it back is how it's written, the critiques are as followed.
-When it comes to dialogue, start a new sentence for different people speaking. Flows better and is easier to understand.
-I would removing the phrase "for example" and similar phrases as it does not add anything.
-there's instances were "then" can be removed without losing anything for the story.
-when writing character action. You should paragraph based on what character is doing what. It's hard to explain but basically, you should have character's talk then act or act then talk. Makes it easier to read.
-there's quite a few spelling and grammar mistakes. I'm not going to list them all.
-Also when there are instances where "anon admired" can be cut out to just have the description.

Sorry if it sounds harsh and I've probably missed a few critiques but I feel just doing this will improve your work immensely. Even just some better paragraphing would help it.

Also if you want some more readers I would advertise your work when you post it. Give a quick blurb and maybe a pic.

Hope to see you around. We all started writing from somewhere.
